Lentulus was descended from a patrician branch of the Cornelian family, one of the most numerous, as well as the most splendid in Rome. His grandfather had borne the title of “ Prince of the Senate,” and was the most active in the pursuit and destruction of C. Grac- chus, in which he received a dangerous wound.
